<L>__{interior meryl's coffee shop day}
<A>__{harry, in a profound state of bereavement, as vita fills a coffee cup in front of him:}
<C>__{vita}
<D>__{what do you want, harry?}
<A>__{without responding, he looks across to the house of bliss.}
<C>__{vita }
<D>__{you want the meatloaf special?}
<A>__{he looks up at her, unable to answer.}
<C>__{vita }
<D>__{chicken pot pie?... tuna melt?}
<A>__{no response.}
<C>__{vita }
<D>__{do you want anything?}
<A>__{he finally answers, but from some place deeply felt and unrelated to the day's specials:}
